So, with radio silence on this problem, I've decided to do some more debugging;

The problem seems to come from `AutoUSBController::GetConfigTable()` at `Controllers/AsusAuraUSBController/AsusAuraUSBController.cpp:109`:

This line of code forces calling the destructor with `delete this`, which causes the openrgb to crash. I'd imagine resource management, in this case the de-allocation, should be handled by whatever constructed this object in the first place, right?
